text: ... and a vestigial fantasy that Big Daddy America will be cross if Europeans make any definite effort to survive.

The best way for America to atone for past ideological crimes would be to publicly recognize it has a strategic interest in post-woke political cultures everywhere (on the model of the new anti-communism), and reward them with tariff relief. Of course, reciprocally, the opposite. ...
... Anyone, anywhere, who stays woke (especially on demographic policy, where the perma-damage is most acute) gets trade taxed for it. Consider it investment in a less deranged world.

... "Betsy has Two Afghan Daddies."
"... and correspondingly unaffordable industrial exports."
Crypto is not the new currency of trade. C'mon. Tariff regimes aren't dependent upon currency dominance in any case.
Japan's not high on the urgent need for therapeutic punishment list.
Thoroughly renouncing the workings of the old regime (as the UK did in 1689) is the key to the rejuvenation of American political culture. Scrapping USAID is already part of this.
The right has no demonstrated ability to keep NGOs bent to its will. All experience points to the opposite conclusion. Subversion is an asymmetric weapon.
